metadata.name: Window gratings 2 #59
metadata.description:
<Window gratings 2> combines 2 images in 1950s: The Window gratings in Taiwan and the Kowloon Walled City in Hong Kong.

Based on the previous experience of <Window gratings>, I rewrite all of the code and give it a totally different perspective.

More than 5,000 possible buildings & floors combinations
Tens of unique Window grating styles, balcony, and roof.
12 different color palette of buildings + 6 background.
3 different color mode lead to totally different images.

metadata.name: Miniscapes #241
metadata.description:
Miniscapes merges generative code (Rich's bit) with meticulously designed scenes and elements (Rick's bit), to create minimalist landscapes intended to charm, delight, and surprise.

Our aim was to convey as much as possible with as little as possible by using simple shapes and lines to represent a wide variety of natural landscapes.

We hope that you find as much joy in owning a Miniscape as we did in creating them.

Controls (in live view):
- Press [s] to save the current image
- Press [p] to pause an animated output
- Press [r] to reset an animated output (this will also pause)

metadata.name: BERNARD #20
metadata.description:
Bernard is a generative character I created.

He loves math/graphing/painting and music.

He draws visuals and music in his own thoughts.

With up to 14 fingers of chord playing, Bernard will solo along with the chords under moderate to slow tempo.

Bernard has 96 editions, aside from the mix-colored version, there are 8 rare Positive and 8 rare Negative.

Be patient with Bernard and enjoy his music and painting.

100% generative audio & visual.

Best experience with Full-screen & Headphones.

Click/Tap as you like if you want to participate in the canvas.

<S> to save image at any moment you like

our consciousness as humans can be distilled into a crudely fashioned hole at an abandoned dave & busters and the meditative state that is endured while sitting on a neglected toilet praying for the sound of disrupted waters. glory holes embody anonymity and pleasure for pleasure's sake. they are creations that cannot be destroyed, as they exist in the memories of anyone who uses or witnesses. many speculate that the carving of the hole is the purest form of human ingenuity and the desire to explore the unknown. formerly limited to the physical space. these glory holes transcend space and time. and exist in that same unknown that tempts us all. legalize ground beef. create nothing. consume everything.

metadata.name: Circles In A Square World #49
metadata.description:
Circles In A Square World, is a play on the saying "being square", usually referring to someone who is more conventional and boring. In the society I grew up in, being square is what people are being pushed towards. A traditional 9 - 5 in a well paying office job the goal. But I believe that in a world where the majority is square, living the circle life is way more fulfilling.

For each square in Circles In A Square World there is a small chance a circle will be drawn instead. The series re-uses the palettes that were discovered in Ode to Color as well. 

To watch the drawing process press 'd'.

To get a higher resolution for printing add ?size=4096 at the end of the URL in the live view (you can use any size you want).

metadata.name: Canevach #56
metadata.description:
Canevach started as a code golfing experiment, 280 characters of HTML, CSS and JavaScript producing pixelated patterns when copy-pasted in the address bar of a web browser.

The code has been adapted for the sake of entropy control and readability, but I tried to keep it as lean as possible to honour the code golfing spirit that initiated the project.

The artwork is generated by manipulating pixels directly through the Canvas API.

Colours are uniformly selected in RGB space, without any colour theory considerations. The only exception is for black, which is made more prominent by the way the algorithm is initiated.

Features
• Canvas size: 8x8 | 16x16 | 32x32 | 64x64 | 128x128
• Number of colours: 1 to 5

metadata.name: fx_doughs #6199
Cubezos – Alpha Series #19
metadata.description:
Cubezos – Alpha Series

Generative art. PFP. Unique. 777.

Cubezos is a play on the artist style of cubism and Tezos. Cubism is abstract, fun, interesting and ignores the norm...That is what I tried to encompass in this project.

There are roughly 150 different traits with 469827993600 different possible combinations. To keep things exciting, there are a dozen or so traits that are a bit “rarer” than the others.

You may see more than one example in the preview window...This is only for preview purposes. You will only be minting one per mint.

Hope you all enjoy the wackiness that is Cubezos!
